The paper deals with the $k$-Cut problem, which is a graph partitioning problem. This suggests that it could belong to categories related to graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CC seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper deals with algorithmic techniques and complexity analysis.
